1
00:00:33,701 --> 00:00:35,035
LOOK AT THOSE
PINE TREES.

2
00:00:35,160 --> 00:00:37,412
AND THAT LAKE.

3
00:00:38,622 --> 00:00:41,917
I SWEAR THAT'S
HONEYSUCKLE I SMELL.

4
00:00:42,041 --> 00:00:45,253
I SWEAR THAT'S A LITTLE
ORANGE BLOSSOM THROWN IN.

5
00:00:45,379 --> 00:00:48,590
IT'S UNBELIEVABLE.
GROWTH,

6
00:00:48,716 --> 00:00:50,175
EXACTLY LIKE THAT
OF EARTH,

7
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:52,553
ON A PLANET
HALF A GALAXY AWAY.

8
00:00:52,678 --> 00:00:54,805
WHAT ARE THE ODDS
ON SUCH DUPLICATION?

9
00:00:54,930 --> 00:00:55,890
ASTRONOMICAL, CAPTAIN.

10
00:00:56,015 --> 00:00:58,976
THE RELATIVE SIZE,
AGE, AND COMPOSITION
OF THIS PLANET

11
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:02,980
MAKES IT HIGHLY IMPROBABLE
THAT IT WOULD EVOLVE
SIMILARLY TO EARTH

12
00:01:03,146 --> 00:01:04,940
IN ANY WAY.

13
00:01:06,316 --> 00:01:08,986
WHAT IN BLAZES
IS THAT?

14
00:01:11,488 --> 00:01:12,322
Kirk:
ANALYSIS, SPOCK.

15
00:01:12,447 --> 00:01:14,867
AN ALIEN METAL
OF SOME KIND.

16
00:01:14,992 --> 00:01:18,119
AN ALLOY RESISTANT
TO PROBE.

17
00:01:18,245 --> 00:01:21,790
READINGS CAN'T EVEN
MEASURE ITS AGE ACCURATELY.

18
00:01:26,503 --> 00:01:28,463
THESE INCISED SYMBOLS
ARE FASCINATING,

19
00:01:28,589 --> 00:01:30,841
EVIDENTLY
SOME FORM OF WRITING.

20
00:01:30,966 --> 00:01:33,010
ANY THEORIES
ABOUT WHAT IT IS?

21
00:01:33,134 --> 00:01:34,762
NEGATIVE, CAPTAIN.

22
00:01:34,887 --> 00:01:36,722
STRUCTURES
OF THIS COMPLEXITY

23
00:01:36,847 --> 00:01:39,433
REQUIRE EXTREMELY
SOPHISTICATED BUILDING
APPARATUS,

24
00:01:39,558 --> 00:01:41,393
THE KIND USUALLY
FOUND IN CULTURES

25
00:01:41,518 --> 00:01:44,063
SURPASSING
OR EQUALING OUR OWN.

26
00:01:44,187 --> 00:01:46,231
MEADOWS
AND NO METEOR CRATERS?

27
00:01:46,356 --> 00:01:48,901
THE WHOLE PLACE IS AN ENIGMA,
BIOLOGICALLY AND CULTURALLY.

28
00:01:49,026 --> 00:01:52,780
WHAT'S THE NEAREST
CONCENTRATION OF LIFE
FORMS, MR. SPOCK?

29
00:01:56,533 --> 00:02:00,328
BEARING 117, MARK 4.

30
00:02:00,454 --> 00:02:02,957
AND HOW MUCH TIME
DID YOU SAY WE HAVE
TO INVESTIGATE?

31
00:02:03,082 --> 00:02:04,708
IF WE ARE TO DIVERT
THE ASTEROID

32
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:06,668
WHICH IS ON A COLLISION
COURSE WITH THIS PLANET,

33
00:02:06,794 --> 00:02:08,921
WE MUST WARP OUT OF ORBIT
WITHIN 30 MINUTES.

34
00:02:09,046 --> 00:02:11,632
EVERY SECOND WE DELAY
ARRIVING AT THE
DEFLECTION POINT

35
00:02:11,757 --> 00:02:15,260
COMPOUNDS THE PROBLEM,
PERHAPS PAST SOLUTION.

36
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:18,221
YOU DID SAY 30 MINUTES?

37
00:02:18,346 --> 00:02:20,849
YES, SIR.

38
00:02:21,892 --> 00:02:23,811
THEN LET'S GO.
LET'S FIND OUT

39
00:02:23,936 --> 00:02:27,731
WHAT LIFE FORMS
ARE BLESSED BY
THIS ENVIRONMENT.

40
00:02:41,036 --> 00:02:44,498
WHY, THEY LOOK LIKE--
I'D SWEAR THEY'RE
AMERICAN INDIANS.

41
00:02:44,623 --> 00:02:45,791
THEY ARE, DOCTOR.

42
00:02:45,916 --> 00:02:49,878
A MIXTURE OF NAVAJO,
MOHICAN, AND DELAWARE,
I BELIEVE.

43
00:02:50,004 --> 00:02:52,840
ALL AMONG
THE MORE ADVANCED
AND PEACEFUL TRIBES.

44
00:02:52,965 --> 00:02:56,010
IT'S LIKE
DISCOVERING ATLANTIS...

45
00:02:56,135 --> 00:02:57,719
OR SHANGRI-LA.

46
00:02:59,513 --> 00:03:01,222
MR. SPOCK,
IS IT POSSIBLE

47
00:03:01,348 --> 00:03:05,393
THERE'S A MORE EVOLVED
CIVILIZATION SOMEWHERE ELSE
ON THIS PLANET,

48
00:03:05,519 --> 00:03:07,437
ONE CAPABLE OF BUILDING
THAT OBELISK

49
00:03:07,562 --> 00:03:10,024
OR DEVELOPING
A DEFLECTOR SYSTEM?

50
00:03:10,149 --> 00:03:11,733
HIGHLY IMPROBABLE,
CAPTAIN.

51
00:03:11,859 --> 00:03:15,320
SENSOR PROBES
INDICATE ONLY ONE TYPE
OF LIFE FORM HERE.

52
00:03:15,445 --> 00:03:17,990
SHOULDN'T WE CONTACT THEM,
JIM, TELL THEM?

53
00:03:18,115 --> 00:03:19,158
TELL THEM WHAT?

54
00:03:19,282 --> 00:03:20,826
THAT AN ASTEROID'S COMING

55
00:03:20,951 --> 00:03:22,786
TO SMASH THEIR WORLD
INTO ATOMS?

56
00:03:22,911 --> 00:03:24,163
TOO PRIMITIVE
TO GRASP THE CONCEPT

57
00:03:24,287 --> 00:03:25,789
OF SPACE FLIGHT,
DOCTOR.

58
00:03:25,914 --> 00:03:27,374
OUR APPEARANCE HERE
WOULD ONLY SERVE

59
00:03:27,499 --> 00:03:29,168
TO CONFUSE
AND FRIGHTEN THEM.

60
00:03:29,292 --> 00:03:31,586
WE'VE GOT A JOB TO DO.

61
00:03:31,712 --> 00:03:33,881
LET'S GET BACK
TO THE<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

62
00:03:44,474 --> 00:03:45,726
WHAT'S THE MATTER, JIM?

63
00:03:45,851 --> 00:03:47,895
WHAT?
OH, NOTHING.

64
00:03:48,020 --> 00:03:50,731
JUST SO PEACEFUL,
UNCOMPLICATED.

65
00:03:50,856 --> 00:03:52,774
NO PROBLEMS, NO...

66
00:03:52,900 --> 00:03:55,194
COMMAND DECISIONS.

67
00:03:55,318 --> 00:03:58,780
JUST...LIVING.

68
00:03:58,906 --> 00:04:00,574
TYPICAL HUMAN REACTION

69
00:04:00,699 --> 00:04:03,911
TO AN IDYLLIC
NATURAL SETTING.

70
00:04:04,036 --> 00:04:06,872
BACK IN THE 20th CENTURY,
WE REFERRED TO IT
AS THE TAHITI SYNDROME.

71
00:04:06,997 --> 00:04:10,625
IT'S PARTICULARLY COMMON
TO OVERPRESSURED
LEADER TYPES,

72
00:04:10,751 --> 00:04:12,293
LIKE STARSHIP CAPTAINS.

73
00:04:12,419 --> 00:04:14,713
AH, TAHITI SYNDROME.

74
00:04:14,838 --> 00:04:16,757
LET'S GO TAKE CARE
OF THAT ASTEROID.

75
00:04:16,882 --> 00:04:20,260
BUT FIRST,
I WANT ANOTHER LOOK
AT THAT OBELISK.

76
00:04:26,141 --> 00:04:27,392
DOCTOR?

77
00:04:27,517 --> 00:04:28,977
YES?

78
00:04:29,103 --> 00:04:30,854
I SUGGEST THAT
ANY FURTHER RESEARCH
ON YOUR PART

79
00:04:30,979 --> 00:04:34,482
BE DELAYED UNTIL
AFTER WE HAVE DIVERTED
THE ASTEROID.

80
00:04:42,950 --> 00:04:44,201
KIRK TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

81
00:04:44,325 --> 00:04:45,452
Scott: YES, SIR.

82
00:05:13,814 --> 00:05:16,775
<i>SPACE--</i>
<i>THE FINAL FRONTIER.</i>

83
00:05:22,656 --> 00:05:26,576
<i>THESE ARE THE VOYAGES</i>
<i>OF THE STARSHIP</i> ENTERPRISE.

84
00:05:26,701 --> 00:05:28,328
<i>ITS FIVE-YEAR MISSION--</i>

85
00:05:28,453 --> 00:05:30,998
<i>TO EXPLORE</i>
<i>STRANGE NEW WORLDS...</i>

86
00:05:31,123 --> 00:05:34,501
<i>TO SEEK OUT NEW LIFE</i>
<i>AND NEW CIVILIZATIONS...</i>

87
00:05:34,626 --> 00:05:38,297
<i>TO BOLDLY GO WHERE</i>
<i>NO MAN HAS GONE BEFORE.</i>

88
00:06:18,377 --> 00:06:21,173
<i>CAPTAIN'S LOG--</i>
<i>STARDATE 4842.6.</i>

89
00:06:21,298 --> 00:06:23,175
<i>FIRST OFFICER SPOCK</i>
<i>COMMANDING.</i>

90
00:06:23,300 --> 00:06:25,177
<i>NUMEROUS SEARCH PARTIES</i>

91
00:06:25,302 --> 00:06:27,512
<i>AND REPEATED SENSOR PROBES</i>
<i>OF THE AREA</i>

92
00:06:27,637 --> 00:06:30,932
<i>HAVE FAILED TO LOCATE</i>
<i>CAPTAIN KIRK.</i>

93
00:06:31,058 --> 00:06:32,517
SPOCK TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

94
00:06:32,642 --> 00:06:33,977
Scott:<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>
COME IN, MR. SPOCK.

95
00:06:34,102 --> 00:06:35,478
PREPARE TO BEAM US UP,
MR. SCOTT.

96
00:06:35,603 --> 00:06:36,521
WE'RE WARPING OUT OF ORBIT.

97
00:06:36,646 --> 00:06:39,524
LEAVING? YOU CAN'T
BE SERIOUS, SPOCK.

98
00:06:39,649 --> 00:06:43,070
DOCTOR, THAT ASTEROID
IS ALMOST AS LARGE

99
00:06:43,195 --> 00:06:44,403
AS YOUR EARTH'S MOON.

100
00:06:44,529 --> 00:06:45,780
FAR ENOUGH AWAY,

101
00:06:45,906 --> 00:06:47,282
THE ANGLE NECESSARY
TO DIVERT IT ENOUGH

102
00:06:47,406 --> 00:06:49,993
TO AVOID DESTRUCTION
IS MINUTE,

103
00:06:50,118 --> 00:06:51,245
BUT AS THE ASTEROID
APPROACHES THIS PLANET,

104
00:06:51,370 --> 00:06:53,580
THE ANGLE BECOMES SO GREAT

105
00:06:53,705 --> 00:06:55,414
THAT EVEN THE POWER
OF A STARSHIP--

106
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:56,708
THE DEVIL
WITH AN ASTEROID!

107
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:58,459
IT WON'T GET HERE
FOR 2 MONTHS, SPOCK!

108
00:06:58,585 --> 00:07:01,546
IF WE ARRIVE AT THE
DEFLECTION POINT IN TIME,

109
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:03,464
IT MAY NOT GET HERE
AT ALL.

110
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:04,507
IN THE MEANTIME,
WHAT ABOUT JIM?

111
00:07:04,632 --> 00:07:06,968
ONCE THE ASTEROID
HAS BEEN DIVERTED,

112
00:07:07,094 --> 00:07:08,303
WE'LL RETURN HERE
AND RESUME THE SEARCH.

113
00:07:08,427 --> 00:07:10,138
THAT MAY BE
HOURS FROM NOW.

114
00:07:10,264 --> 00:07:11,639
HE MAY BE INJURED
OR DYING.

115
00:07:15,269 --> 00:07:17,396
DOCTOR...

116
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:20,148
ASSUME THIS IS
THE PLANET WE'RE ON.

117
00:07:20,274 --> 00:07:22,901
THIS IS THE APPROACHING
ASTEROID.

118
00:07:23,026 --> 00:07:25,737
IF WE DON'T GET
TO THAT DEFLECTION
POINT IN TIME,

119
00:07:25,862 --> 00:07:30,033
IT WILL BECOME
PHYSICALLY IMPOSSIBLE
TO DIVERT THIS ASTEROID.

120
00:07:30,158 --> 00:07:33,578
IN THAT CASE, EVERYONE
ON THIS PLANET WILL DIE,

121
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:35,414
INCLUDING THE CAPTAIN.

122
00:07:35,538 --> 00:07:37,457
CAN A FEW MORE MINUTES
MATTER, SPOCK?

123
00:07:37,582 --> 00:07:40,460
IN THE TIME
IT HAS TAKEN ME
TO EXPLAIN THE PROBLEM,

124
00:07:40,585 --> 00:07:43,588
THE ASTEROID
HAS MOVED FROM HERE
TO HERE.

125
00:07:43,713 --> 00:07:46,591
THE LONGER WE DELAY,
THE LESS THE LIKELIHOOD

126
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:48,927
OF BEING ABLE
TO DIVERT IT.

127
00:07:58,686 --> 00:08:00,521
BEAM US UP, MR. SCOTT.

128
00:08:09,614 --> 00:08:11,074
<i>[THINKING]</i>
<i>WHERE AM I?</i>

129
00:08:11,199 --> 00:08:13,285
<i>WHAT PLACE IS THIS?</i>

130
00:08:23,503 --> 00:08:25,088
<i>WHAT ARE THESE?</i>

131
00:08:25,213 --> 00:08:27,632
<i>I FEEL I SHOULD KNOW.</i>

132
00:08:27,757 --> 00:08:30,135
<i>THEY'RE FAMILIAR</i>

133
00:08:30,260 --> 00:08:32,762
<i>AND YET UNFAMILIAR.</i>

134
00:08:34,181 --> 00:08:36,350
<i>HOW DID I GET HERE?</i>

135
00:08:37,058 --> 00:08:39,102
<i>WHO AM I?</i>

136
00:08:39,227 --> 00:08:41,855
<i>TRY TO REMEMBER.</i>

137
00:09:11,176 --> 00:09:12,386
WAIT.

138
00:09:53,051 --> 00:09:55,303
WHO ARE YOU?

139
00:09:57,097 --> 00:09:58,890
WE ARE YOUR PEOPLE.

140
00:09:59,015 --> 00:10:02,519
WE'VE BEEN WAITING
FOR YOU TO COME TO US.

141
00:10:08,942 --> 00:10:11,486
<i>CAPTAIN'S LOG--</i>
<i>STARDATE 4843.6.</i>

142
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:14,406
<i>FIRST OFFICER SPOCK</i>
<i>COMMANDING.</i>

143
00:10:14,531 --> 00:10:17,784
<i>WE'VE BEEN EN ROUTE</i>
<i>TO THE ASTEROID</i>
<i>FOR SEVERAL HOURS.</i>

144
00:10:17,909 --> 00:10:19,286
<i>OUR DELAY</i>
<i>ON THE PLANET'S SURFACE</i>

145
00:10:19,411 --> 00:10:23,123
<i>HAS MADE IT IMPERATIVE</i>
<i>THAT WE PROCEED</i>
<i>AT MAXIMUM WARP SPEED</i>

146
00:10:23,248 --> 00:10:26,709
<i>FOR A PERIOD WHICH EXCEEDS</i>
<i>THE RECOMMENDED SAFETY MARGIN.</i>

147
00:10:26,834 --> 00:10:30,589
I CAN'T GIVE YOU WARP 9
MUCH LONGER, MR. SPOCK.

148
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:33,425
THESE ENGINES ARE BEGINNING
TO SHOW SIGNS OF STRESS.

149
00:10:33,550 --> 00:10:36,052
STRESS OR NOT,
WE CANNOT REDUCE SPEED.

150
00:10:36,177 --> 00:10:37,971
I DO NOT INTEND TO MISS
THAT DEFLECTION POINT.

151
00:10:38,096 --> 00:10:40,807
ALL RIGHT. BUT WE'RE
MOVING FURTHER
INTO THE DANGER RANGE

152
00:10:40,932 --> 00:10:42,183
ALL THE TIME.
IF THESE CIRCUITS--

153
00:10:42,309 --> 00:10:43,851
OBJECTION NOTED,
MR. SCOTT.

154
00:10:43,977 --> 00:10:46,104
CARRY ON.

155
00:11:00,410 --> 00:11:03,246
MIRAMANEE HAS SAID
THAT YOU APPEARED TO HER

156
00:11:03,371 --> 00:11:06,958
AND TO HER HANDMAIDEN
FROM THE WALLS
OF THE TEMPLE,

157
00:11:07,083 --> 00:11:09,252
JUST AS OUR LEGEND
FORETELLS.

158
00:11:09,377 --> 00:11:12,380
WE DO NOT DOUBT
THE WORDS
OF OUR PRIESTESS,

159
00:11:12,506 --> 00:11:14,090
BUT THESE
ARE TROUBLED TIMES

160
00:11:14,215 --> 00:11:16,259
AND WE MUST BE SURE.

161
00:11:16,384 --> 00:11:18,428
I'LL ANSWER ANYTHING
I CAN,

162
00:11:18,553 --> 00:11:19,678
BUT AS I TOLD YOU...

163
00:11:19,804 --> 00:11:23,141
MANY THINGS
ARE STRANGE TO ME.

164
00:11:23,266 --> 00:11:26,102
HE KNOWS NOTHING
OF OUR DANGER.
HOW COULD HE SAVE US?

165
00:11:26,227 --> 00:11:30,524
IT IS AGAINST CUSTOM
TO INTERRUPT A TRIBAL ELDER
AT COUNCIL,

166
00:11:30,649 --> 00:11:32,651
EVEN FOR THE MEDICINE CHIEF.

167
00:11:32,775 --> 00:11:35,153
ELDER,
WORDS WILL NOT SAVE US
WHEN THE SKIES DARKEN.

168
00:11:35,278 --> 00:11:37,030
WE MUST BE CERTAIN.

169
00:11:37,155 --> 00:11:39,616
I SAY HE MUST PROVE
HE IS A GOD.

170
00:11:40,908 --> 00:11:43,077
OUR SKIES HAVE DARKENED

171
00:11:43,203 --> 00:11:45,455
3 TIMES
SINCE THE HARVEST,

172
00:11:45,580 --> 00:11:47,748
THE LAST TIME
WORST OF ALL.

173
00:11:47,874 --> 00:11:50,585
OUR LEGEND PREDICTS
SUCH DANGER

174
00:11:50,709 --> 00:11:53,963
AND PROMISES
THAT THE WISE ONES
WHO PLANTED US HERE

175
00:11:54,088 --> 00:11:55,882
WILL SEND A GOD

176
00:11:56,007 --> 00:11:57,467
TO SAVE US,

177
00:11:57,592 --> 00:12:00,428
ONE WHO CAN ROUSE
THE TEMPLE SPIRIT

178
00:12:00,554 --> 00:12:02,472
AND MAKE THE SKY
GROW QUIET.

179
00:12:02,597 --> 00:12:04,558
CAN YOU DO THIS?

180
00:12:11,856 --> 00:12:15,734
I CAME FROM THE TEMPLE
AS MIRAMANEE SAID,

181
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:22,033
AND IT WAS
A BEGINNING FOR ME...HERE.

182
00:12:23,368 --> 00:12:25,786
BUT I CAME FROM THE SKY...

183
00:12:25,912 --> 00:12:27,955
TOO.

184
00:12:28,747 --> 00:12:32,960
ONLY I...CAN'T REMEMBER.

185
00:12:34,254 --> 00:12:35,714
I...

186
00:12:35,838 --> 00:12:37,257
I CAN'T REMEMBER.

187
00:12:38,299 --> 00:12:40,552
SALISH, A TERRIBLE THING
HAS HAPPENED.

188
00:12:40,677 --> 00:12:43,137
THE BOY WAS ATTENDING
THE FISH NETS.

189
00:12:43,263 --> 00:12:46,057
HE BECAME ENTANGLED IN THEM
AND SANK TO THE BOTTOM
OF THE RIVER.

190
00:12:46,182 --> 00:12:50,019
LUMO BROUGHT HIM UP QUICKLY,
BUT HE DOESN'T MOVE.

191
00:12:57,110 --> 00:13:00,739
THERE IS NO SOUND
IN THE BODY.

192
00:13:00,863 --> 00:13:03,116
THERE IS NO LIGHT
IN THE EYES.

193
00:13:03,241 --> 00:13:05,034
HE WILL MOVE NO MORE.

194
00:13:05,159 --> 00:13:06,953
WAIT A MOMENT.

195
00:13:44,865 --> 00:13:46,159
WAIT!

196
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:54,626
[COUGHS]

197
00:14:04,427 --> 00:14:06,429
HE'LL BE ALL RIGHT NOW.

198
00:14:06,554 --> 00:14:08,348
MY PEOPLE ARE GRATEFUL.

199
00:14:10,266 --> 00:14:12,143
IT'S A SIMPLE TECHNIQUE.

200
00:14:12,268 --> 00:14:13,645
IT GOES WAY BACK...

201
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:19,066
WAY BACK...

202
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:23,863
ONLY A GOD
CAN BREATHE LIFE
INTO THE DEAD.

203
00:14:25,239 --> 00:14:27,575
DO YOU STILL QUESTION?

204
00:14:33,623 --> 00:14:36,167
GIVE HIM
THE MEDICINE BADGE.

205
00:15:32,223 --> 00:15:34,934
Chekov:
DEFLECTION POINT MINUS 7.

206
00:15:35,059 --> 00:15:36,811
Spock:
FULL POWER, MR. SCOTT.

207
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:39,606
THE RELAYS WILL REJECT
THE OVERLOAD, MR. SPOCK.

208
00:15:39,731 --> 00:15:41,399
THEN BYPASS THE RELAYS,
GO TO MANUAL CONTROL.

209
00:15:41,524 --> 00:15:43,401
DO THAT, WE'LL BURN
OUT THE ENGINES.

210
00:15:43,526 --> 00:15:45,779
I WANT FULL POWER,
MR. SCOTT.

211
00:15:45,904 --> 00:15:47,154
AYE, SIR.

212
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:49,323
ALL RIGHT, YOU LOVELIES,

213
00:15:49,449 --> 00:15:51,158
HOLD TOGETHER.

214
00:15:55,413 --> 00:15:57,123
FULL POWER,
MR. SPOCK.

215
00:15:57,248 --> 00:15:58,958
MAGNIFICATION FACTOR 12,
MR. SULU.

216
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:00,627
AYE, SIR.

217
00:16:08,175 --> 00:16:11,262
DEFLECTION POINT
MINUS 4.

218
00:16:11,387 --> 00:16:12,639
ALL ENGINES STOPPED.

219
00:16:12,764 --> 00:16:14,474
HOLD POSITION HERE.

220
00:16:20,229 --> 00:16:22,732
ALL ENGINES STOPPED, SIR.

221
00:16:22,857 --> 00:16:24,692
PREPARE TO ACTIVATE
DEFLECTORS.

222
00:16:24,818 --> 00:16:26,820
AYE, SIR.

223
